This beautiful shape was designed by LilaLoa, a well known cookie artist. Use for Valentine's Day, weddings, the Rose Bowl, or any other occasion where a rose takes center stage.


ABOUT THE DESIGNER
Georganne Bell is the sugar artist behind the cookie decorating blog LilaLoa. She began her journey into sugar through cakes, but quickly switched to cookies when she moved to South Korea and discovered that her oven was the size of a bread box. A mix of innovation, science, and sugar, she continues to create cookies, design cutters, and teach local cookie decorating classes while raising her four young children and avoiding laundry at all costs.

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: NEW! This 3 1/2" shape- the craze of 2017- may not spin as well as the real thing, but it will be an amusing way to impress your friends! Decorate your Fidget Spinner cookies to look just like YOUR spinner.

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: Please give us a 3 1/4" Letter P Cookie Cutter. Goes well with Thank You and You're Welcome. Teach a child proper manners, and then devour the cookies and leave crumbs all over the counter.

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4:
NEW! Squirrel away this 3 1/2" Acorn cookie cutter for the fall harvest! Cut out & decorate cookies, or use the shape for other crafts. Also makes a cute back-to-school gift for a teacher.

Cookies decorated by LilaLoa.

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: NEW! Teach your child the alphabet with our 3 1/4" Letter B Cookie Cutter. You won't have to wait for Sesame Street! You could also use the cookie cutter as a wedding favor, to cut out cookies for favors, or for a graduation party.

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: NEW! F is for fun, friendship, and anyone who has a name beginning with the letter F! Ideal for a child's birthday party or to teach the alphabet.

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: Let them eat cake! The 3 3/4" Wedding Cake Cookie Cutter is ideal for cutting out wedding cookies, especially if you want something a little different from the traditional tiered cake. There are endless ways to decorate these cookies. This shape is also great for a bridal shower, or for crafting projects. Made in the USA.

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: Feel a tropical breeze with the Palm Tree Cookie Cutter. Make a platter of cookies with the Sunglasses, Bikini Top & Bottom, and Dolphin, and feel like it's summer- even when it's miserably cold outside.

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: Embrace the magic of the holiday season with the 4" Snowglobe Cookie Cutter. There are innumerable ways to decorate these cookies- dress them up for Christmas, Hanukkah, or just winter in general. Impress your friends by bringing these to a party instead of fruitcake or brownies!

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: Fans of Charlie Brown's shirt will dig the 5 1/4" Chevron Pattern Cookie Cutter. Use this cutter as a stencil for crafting, or cut out a fondant design for a cake. Those are just two of MANY uses of this shape! The Chevron was redesigned in 2017.

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: NEW! Blast off with the 4" x 2 3/8" Rocket Cookie Cutter. Blast Elton John's "Rocket Man" as you share some Rocket cookies with your kids- or just eat them all yourself!

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: NEW! Plug in the lights- it's Christmas time! The 3 1/4" Christmas Light Bulb Cookie Cutter will brighten up any holiday bash. Decorate the cookies with a variety of colors and get snackin'.

column3: (All) Ann Clark Cookie Cutters|Metal Cookie Cutters
column4: NEW! It's ok to goof around with this 4 1/2" x 2 1/2" cookie cutter- it's not fragile! The Christmas Leg Lamp is sure to get a few laughs and is a great choice for a party. Also fun to give as a gag gift or stocking stuffer.

NEW!
Celebrate any occasion with the 4 1/8" LilaLoa's Confetti cookie cutter! From graduation to New Year's Eve, this shape will add pizzazz to your gathering. Plus, unlike real confetti, there's no need for post-party vacuuming!


ABOUT THE DESIGNER
Georganne Bell is the sugar artist behind the cookie decorating blog LilaLoa. She began her journey into sugar through cakes, but quickly switched to cookies when she moved to South Korea and discovered that her oven was the size of a bread box. A mix of innovation, science, and sugar, she continues to create cookies, design cutters, and teach local cookie decorating classes while raising her four young children and avoiding laundry at all costs.
Size: 4 1/8" x 1 7/8"

NEW!
If you're all about the plaque, try our 2 7/8" Small Fanciful Plaque by SweetAmbs. Add flair to any occasion with this simple yet elegant shape! Ideal for weddings, anniversaries, birthdays, and more.


ABOUT THE DESIGNER
Amber Spiegel is the pastry chef and cookie artist known as SweetAmbs. A graduate of the Baking and Pastry Program at The Culinary Institute of America, grand prize winner of Wilton's 2008 cake decorating contest and graduate of Wilton's Master Course in Cake Decorating and Confectionary Art, Amber has focused her confectionary talents towards educating others. Amber now produces cookie decorating video tutorials and travels the world to teach others how to make beautiful cookies on their own. Her work has been featured in several magazines including Martha Stewart Weddings, InStyle, Your Wedding Day, Cake Central, Brides, as well as on numerous Internet blogs and websites including Buzzfeed, Junebug Weddings, Merci New York, and The Huffington Post.
See more of Amber's work at www.SweetAmbs.com.

NEW! A child's fourth birthday would be incomplete without the 3 1/4" Number 4 Cookie Cutter! This shape also works for any occasion that calls for a #4, from graduations to anniversaries. Make number 4 cookies with abandon.
NEW! Celebrate a birthday, graduation, anniversary, and any other special occasion with the Number 8 Cookie Cutter. Also great for sports parties or for a Magic 8 ball theme!

NEW! Rawr! Fans of Jurassic Park will dig our T-Rex Cookie Cutter. It's not as terrifying as the real deal, but it's perfect for cookies for a birthday party. Decorate it to be scary or girly, and take a bite!

NEW! Celebrate a birthday, anniversary, graduation, and more with our Number 6 & 9 Cookie Cutter. This shape functions as both a six and a nine, depending on how you flip it. Make number 6 cookies and number 9 cookies for birthdays, anniversaries, graduations, sporting events and other special occasions.
NEW! This old-fashioned pickup truck with Christmas tree cookie cutter is perfect for those nostalgic for the holidays of yesteryear. This shape is great for cookie swaps or holiday parties.
NEW! No geometry knowledge necessary to use the Geometric Plaque Cookie Cutter. Use to decorate southwest-style cookies; trace designs for crafting; or create cookie "tiles"!
NEW! You don't have to be a puzzle mastermind to enjoy this cookie cutter! Make cookies in this shape to surprise a puzzle-loving friend. There's no logic involved in eating cookies!
NEW! Make a traditional gingerbread house, or give a loved one a "welcome home" gift, with the Gingerbread House cookie cutter. Works well for Christmas, Hanukkah, realtors, and beyond!

NEW! Calling all dinosaur lovers! Try the Triceratops Cookie Cutter for cut-out cookies and crafts. This is a fun shape for kids and adults alike, and will be a welcome addition to a dinosaur collection.

NEW! Live goldfish may have a very short lifespan, but our 3" Gold Fish Cookie Cutter will "live" for many years. It's much more fun than a pet rock, but not nearly as demanding as a dog or cat. Use this cookie cutter for a Finding Nemo-themed birthday party, or for someone who likes fishing!
NEW! Whether it's the key to your heart, or a house key, the Key Cookie Cutter is quite versatile. Makes an ideal gift for new homeowners, or as a symbol of love to your one and only.

NEW!
A picture is worth 1,000 cookies with the Camera Cookie Cutter, designed by the extraordinary cookie artist Anne Yorks at Flour Box Bakery. You won't need a flash or lens to make cookies with this shape!
Cookies decorated by Flour Box Bakery.
ABOUT THE DESIGNER
Anne Yorks is the owner and head decorator of Flour Box Bakery LLC. She started decorating cookies in 2007 when she left the 'real world' to be a stay-at-home mom and pursue her dreams of owning and operating her own company. A baker since a very young age, Anne is self-taught and has perfected her cookies and recipes over years of trial and error. She has taught two online Craftsy classes and loves to teach live classes in her cookie studio in Bellefonte, PA.
